South Africa Stocks Rise Most in Close to Two Weeks as Commodities Rally

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-16T07:40:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/south-african-stocks-climb-most-in-two-weeks-as-commodity-prices-increase.html
South African stocks rose the most
in close to two weeks, led by Anglo American Plc, as commodities
rose on expectation reconstruction in  Japan  after its biggest
quake on record will raise demand, boosting miners.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index climbed as much as 1.1
percent to 30,525.37 and traded 1 percent up at 30,502.53 by
9:37 a.m. in Johannesburg. Anglo American, part owner of the
worldâ€™s biggest platinum and diamond producers, rallied as much
as 2.2 percent to 344.79 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
